# torch_ios: skip the 94 quantized schemas that reference custom classes
# (Conv2dPackedParamsBase, LinearPackedParamsBase, EmbeddingPackedParamsBase).
#
# Symptom (without patch): torch import crashes inside dyld static-init
# of libtorch_python.dylib with
#   torch::jit::ErrorReport: Unknown custom class type
#     quantized.Conv2dPackedParamsBase. Please ensure it is registered.:
#   quantized::conv1d(Tensor qx, ... .Conv2dPackedParamsBase ...) -> Tensor
#                                          ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ <--- HERE
#
# Root cause: TORCH_LIBRARY(quantized, m) calls register_conv_params<2/3>()
# etc. at the top of its body, which register the custom classes via
# function-local statics. On Linux that ordering is reliable. On iOS dyld 4
# the static-init handshake doesn't reliably fire before the schema parser
# inside the same body looks them up — and the resulting ErrorReport
# bypasses every catch handler we tried (init_priority(101), constructor
# attribute, noinline + try/catch, even catch(...)) because dyld 4's
# static-init phase doesn't allow C++ exception unwinding past the
# initializer boundary — the throw is dispatched directly to
# std::terminate via __cxa_get_exception_ptr without ever calling the
# personality function for the wrapper frame.
#
# We don't actually call any quantized conv/linear/embedding ops on iPad
# (those would need fbgemm or qnnpack runtime kernels we haven't tested).
# So the simplest robust fix is to just drop the schemas that need the
# custom classes. The C++ implementations stay (TORCH_LIBRARY_IMPL blocks
# in qconv*.cpp etc.) — they just won't have schemas to attach to. Calls
# to quantized.conv1d at Python-level get a clean OperatorNotFound error,
# not a process abort.
#
# 94 schemas filtered via:
#   sed -i '/m\.def(.*PackedParamsBase/s|^|//torch_ios:SKIPPED |' library.cpp

# This patch isn't a unified diff — it's a sed transformation. Apply with:
#   cd torch_ios/build/pytorch && \
#     sed -i.bak '/m\.def(.*PackedParamsBase/s|^|//torch_ios:SKIPPED |' \
#       aten/src/ATen/native/quantized/library.cpp && \
#     rm aten/src/ATen/native/quantized/library.cpp.bak
